verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the Lord; and the Lord delivered them into the hand of the Philistines forty years.
verses.verse_html:
1And the children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the Lord; and the Lord delivered them into the hand of the Philistines forty years. ▼
▼ did evil…: Heb. added to commit, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ did evil…: Heb. added to commit, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ did evil…: Heb. added to commit, etc

verses.text_plain: And there was a certain man of Zorah, of the family of the Danites, whose name was Manoah; and his wife was barren, and bare not.
verses.verse_html: 2And there was a certain man of Zorah, of the family of the Danites, whose name was Manoah; and his wife was barren, and bare not.

verses.text_plain: And the angel of the Lord appeared unto the woman, and said unto her, Behold now, thou art barren, and bearest not: but thou shalt conceive, and bear a son.
verses.verse_html: 3And the angel of the Lord appeared unto the woman, and said unto her, Behold now, thou art barren, and bearest not: but thou shalt conceive, and bear a son.

verses.text_plain: Now therefore beware, I pray thee, and drink not wine nor strong drink, and eat not any unclean thing:
verses.verse_html: 4Now therefore beware, I pray thee, and drink not wine nor strong drink, and eat not any unclean thing:

verses.text_plain: For, lo, thou shalt conceive, and bear a son; and no razor shall come on his head: for the child shall be a Nazarite unto God from the womb: and he shall begin to deliver Israel out of the hand of the Philistines.
verses.verse_html: 5For, lo, thou shalt conceive, and bear a son; and no razor shall come on his head: for the child shall be a Nazarite unto God from the womb: and he shall begin to deliver Israel out of the hand of the Philistines.

verses.text_plain: Then the woman came and told her husband, saying, A man of God came unto me, and his countenance was like the countenance of an angel of God, very terrible: but I asked him not whence he was, neither told he me his name:
verses.verse_html: 6Then the woman came and told her husband, saying, A man of God came unto me, and his countenance was like the countenance of an angel of God, very terrible: but I asked him not whence he was, neither told he me his name:

verses.text_plain: But he said unto me, Behold, thou shalt conceive, and bear a son; and now drink no wine nor strong drink, neither eat any unclean thing: for the child shall be a Nazarite to God from the womb to the day of his death.
verses.verse_html: 7But he said unto me, Behold, thou shalt conceive, and bear a son; and now drink no wine nor strong drink, neither eat any unclean thing: for the child shall be a Nazarite to God from the womb to the day of his death.

tokens.text: unto me, Behold, thou shalt conceive

verses.text_plain: Then Manoah intreated the Lord, and said, O my Lord, let the man of God which thou didst send come again unto us, and teach us what we shall do unto the child that shall be born.
verses.verse_html: 8Then Manoah intreated the Lord, and said, O my Lord, let the man of God which thou didst send come again unto us, and teach us what we shall do unto the child that shall be born.

verses.text_plain: And God hearkened to the voice of Manoah; and the angel of God came again unto the woman as she sat in the field: but Manoah her husband was not with her.
verses.verse_html: 9And God hearkened to the voice of Manoah; and the angel of God came again unto the woman as she sat in the field: but Manoah her husband was not with her.

verses.text_plain: And the woman made haste, and ran, and shewed her husband, and said unto him, Behold, the man hath appeared unto me, that came unto me the other day.
verses.verse_html: 10And the woman made haste, and ran, and shewed her husband, and said unto him, Behold, the man hath appeared unto me, that came unto me the other day.

verses.text_plain: And Manoah arose, and went after his wife, and came to the man, and said unto him, Art thou the man that spakest unto the woman? And he said, I am.
verses.verse_html: 11And Manoah arose, and went after his wife, and came to the man, and said unto him, Art thou the man that spakest unto the woman? And he said, I am.

verses.text_plain: And Manoah said, Now let thy words come to pass. How shall we order the child, and how shall we do unto him?
verses.verse_html:
12And Manoah said, Now let thy words come to pass. How shall we order the child, and how shall we do unto him? ▼
▼ How shall we order…: Heb. What shall be the manner of the, etc
 , ▼
▼ how shall we do…: or, what shall he do?: Heb. what shall be his work?

verses.text_plain: And the angel of the Lord said unto Manoah, Of all that I said unto the woman let her beware.
verses.verse_html: 13And the angel of the Lord said unto Manoah, Of all that I said unto the woman let her beware.

verses.text_plain: She may not eat of any thing that cometh of the vine, neither let her drink wine or strong drink, nor eat any unclean thing: all that I commanded her let her observe.
verses.verse_html: 14She may not eat of any thing that cometh of the vine, neither let her drink wine or strong drink, nor eat any unclean thing: all that I commanded her let her observe.

verses.text_plain: And Manoah said unto the angel of the Lord, I pray thee, let us detain thee, until we shall have made ready a kid for thee.
verses.verse_html:
15And Manoah said unto the angel of the Lord, I pray thee, let us detain thee, until we shall have made ready a kid for thee. ▼
▼ for thee: Heb. before thee

tokens.text: I pray thee, let us detain
thee, until we shall have made ready

footnotes.body_html: ▼ for thee: Heb. before thee

verses.text_plain: And the angel of the Lord said unto Manoah, Though thou detain me, I will not eat of thy bread: and if thou wilt offer a burnt offering, thou must offer it unto the Lord. For Manoah knew not that he was an angel of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16And the angel of the Lord said unto Manoah, Though thou detain me, I will not eat of thy bread: and if thou wilt offer a burnt offering, thou must offer it unto the Lord. For Manoah knew not that he was an angel of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And Manoah said unto the angel of the Lord, What is thy name, that when thy sayings come to pass we may do thee honour?
verses.verse_html: 17And Manoah said unto the angel of the Lord, What is thy name, that when thy sayings come to pass we may do thee honour?

verses.text_plain: And the angel of the Lord said unto him, Why askest thou thus after my name, seeing it is secret?
verses.verse_html:
18And the angel of the Lord said unto him, Why askest thou thus after my name, seeing it is secret? ▼
▼ secret: or, wonderful

verses.text_plain: So Manoah took a kid with a meat offering, and offered it upon a rock unto the Lord: and the angel did wondrously; and Manoah and his wife looked on.
verses.verse_html: 19So Manoah took a kid with a meat offering, and offered it upon a rock unto the Lord: and the angel did wondrously; and Manoah and his wife looked on.

verses.text_plain: For it came to pass, when the flame went up toward heaven from off the altar, that the angel of the Lord ascended in the flame of the altar. And Manoah and his wife looked on it, and fell on their faces to the ground.
verses.verse_html: 20For it came to pass, when the flame went up toward heaven from off the altar, that the angel of the Lord ascended in the flame of the altar. And Manoah and his wife looked on it, and fell on their faces to the ground.

tokens.text: For it came to pass, when the flame

verses.text_plain: But the angel of the Lord did no more appear to Manoah and to his wife. Then Manoah knew that he was an angel of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 21But the angel of the Lord did no more appear to Manoah and to his wife. Then Manoah knew that he was an angel of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And Manoah said unto his wife, We shall surely die, because we have seen God.
verses.verse_html: 22And Manoah said unto his wife, We shall surely die, because we have seen God.

verses.text_plain: But his wife said unto him, If the Lord were pleased to kill us, he would not have received a burnt offering and a meat offering at our hands, neither would he have shewed us all these things, nor would as at this time have told us such things as these.
verses.verse_html: 23But his wife said unto him, If the Lord were pleased to kill us, he would not have received a burnt offering and a meat offering at our hands, neither would he have shewed us all these things, nor would as at this time have told us such things as these.

tokens.text: us, he would not have received
nor would as at this time

verses.text_plain: And the woman bare a son, and called his name Samson: and the child grew, and the Lord blessed him.
verses.verse_html: 24And the woman bare a son, and called his name Samson: and the child grew, and the Lord blessed him.

verses.text_plain: And the Spirit of the Lord began to move him at times in the camp of Dan between Zorah and Eshtaol.
verses.verse_html:
25And the Spirit of the Lord began to move him at times in the camp of Dan between Zorah and Eshtaol. ▼
▼ the camp…: Heb. Mahaneh–dan

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the camp…: Heb. Mahaneh–dan
